00:00:12.146 --> 00:00:13.824
 I will never forget that day 

00:00:13.824 --> 00:00:17.723
 of the spring of 2006. 

00:00:17.723 --> 00:00:19.302
 I was a resident surgeon 

00:00:19.302 --> 00:00:21.733
 at Johns Hopkins Hospital 

00:00:21.733 --> 00:00:23.510
 in accepting emergency calls. 

00:00:23.510 --> 00:00:26.873
 Around 2 a.m. I was notified by ER 

00:00:26.873 --> 00:00:28.900
 to go see a woman with diabetic ulcer 

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:30.694
 at her feet. 

00:00:30.694 --> 00:00:34.395
 I still remember that kind of rotten blood smell, 

00:00:34.395 --> 00:00:38.022
 as I was pulling the curtain to see it. 

00:00:38.022 --> 00:00:40.367
 Everyone there thought that woman was very ill 

00:00:40.367 --> 00:00:41.719
 and needed to be hospitalized. 

00:00:41.719 --> 00:00:43.319
 This was not discussed. 

00:00:43.319 --> 00:00:45.461
 The question I posed was another, 

00:00:45.461 --> 00:00:49.390
 did she need amputation? 

00:00:49.390 --> 00:00:52.357
 Now, turning our heads back to that night 

00:00:52.357 --> 00:00:57.522
 I would desperately want to believe that I treated that woman, 

00:00:57.522 --> 00:01:00.658
 that night, with the same empathy and compassion 

00:01:00.658 --> 00:01:04.893
 which I showed to the 27-year-old newlywed 

00:01:04.893 --> 00:01:06.838
 which came to ER three days ago 

00:01:06.838 --> 00:01:08.452
 with low back pain 

00:01:08.452 --> 00:01:12.701
 which turned out to be advanced pancreatic cancer. 

00:01:12.701 --> 00:01:14.864
 In her case, I knew there was nothing I could do 

00:01:14.864 --> 00:01:16.632
 that would save his life. 

00:01:16.632 --> 00:01:18.681
 The cancer was very advanced. 

00:01:18.681 --> 00:01:21.361
 But I was committed to making sure that 

00:01:21.361 --> 00:01:23.784
 I would do everything possible to make her feel 

00:01:23.784 --> 00:01:26.207
 more comfortable. I brought him a warm blanket 

00:01:26.207 --> 00:01:28.927
 and a cup of coffee. 

00:01:28.927 --> 00:01:31.112
 I also brought it to her parents. 

00:01:31.112 --> 00:01:34.258
 But look, the most important thing is that I didnâ€™t prejudice him, 

00:01:34.258 --> 00:01:36.155
 because it was clear that she had done nothing 

00:01:36.155 --> 00:01:38.329
 that could cause this to itself. 

00:01:38.329 --> 00:01:41.142
 Then, how is it possible that a few nights later, 

00:01:41.142 --> 00:01:44.300
 to stay in the same emergency room and set 

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:47.711
 that my diabetic patient needed amputation, 

00:01:47.711 --> 00:01:51.615
 why did I say that in such a bitter way? 

00:01:51.615 --> 00:01:54.080
 The difference is that in contrast to the woman the night before, 

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.479
 this woman suffered from type 2 diabetes. 

00:01:56.479 --> 00:01:58.031
 She was healthy. 

00:01:58.031 --> 00:01:59.944
 And we all know that this comes as a result of eating too much 

00:01:59.944 --> 00:02:02.299
 and lack of physical activity, right? 

00:02:02.299 --> 00:02:04.983
 I mean, how hard can it be? 

00:02:04.983 --> 00:02:07.344
 As I watched him lie down I thought to myself, 

00:02:07.344 --> 00:02:10.232
 as if you cared very little, 

00:02:10.232 --> 00:02:13.222
 you would not be in this state now 

00:02:13.222 --> 00:02:14.999
 with a doctor you had never seen before 

00:02:14.999 --> 00:02:18.814
 preparing to cut your leg. 

00:02:18.814 --> 00:02:22.456
 Why did I feel justified in judging her? 

00:02:22.456 --> 00:02:25.025
 I would like to say that I do not know. 

00:02:25.025 --> 00:02:27.061
 But this is not true. 

00:02:27.061 --> 00:02:29.392
 With the pride of my youth, 

00:02:29.392 --> 00:02:32.496
 I thought I had psychologized it. 

00:02:32.496 --> 00:02:34.326
 She has eaten a lot. She has been unlucky. 

00:02:34.326 --> 00:02:37.695
 He contracted diabetes. That's the job. 

00:02:37.695 --> 00:02:39.098
 Strangely, at that time, 

00:02:39.098 --> 00:02:41.496
 I was researching cancer, 

00:02:41.496 --> 00:02:43.839
 immune system therapies for skin cancer, to be more precise, 

00:02:43.839 --> 00:02:47.812
 from which I had learned that I should have doubts about everything, 

00:02:47.812 --> 00:02:49.848
 not to take anything for granted 

00:02:49.848 --> 00:02:53.658
 and to measure with the highest scientific standards. 

00:02:53.658 --> 00:02:57.034
 Meanwhile, when it comes to diabetes 

00:02:57.034 --> 00:03:00.583
 which kills 8 times more Americans than melanoma, 

00:03:00.583 --> 00:03:04.011
 I never put the knowledge to the test until then. 

00:03:04.011 --> 00:03:07.057
 I accepted the welcome, 

00:03:07.057 --> 00:03:09.642
 every link in the chain of pathological causes that led to it. 

00:03:09.642 --> 00:03:13.042
 Three years later, I discovered that I was very wrong. 

00:03:13.042 --> 00:03:15.642
 But this time, I was the patient. 

00:03:15.642 --> 00:03:19.473
 Although I exercised 3-4 hours a day, 

00:03:19.473 --> 00:03:22.038
 and the implementation of precision food pyramids, 

00:03:22.038 --> 00:03:24.195
 I had gained a lot of weight and developed 

00:03:24.195 --> 00:03:26.480
 something called metabolic syndrome. 

00:03:26.480 --> 00:03:28.464
 Some of you may have heard of it. 

00:03:28.464 --> 00:03:31.909
 I was immune to insulin. 

00:03:31.909 --> 00:03:34.358
 You can think of insulin as this all-powerful hormone 

00:03:34.358 --> 00:03:38.421
 that controls what our body does with the foods we eat, 

00:03:38.421 --> 00:03:40.535
 if we store or burn them. 

00:03:40.535 --> 00:03:43.349
 In medical parlance this is called "energy sharing". 

00:03:43.349 --> 00:03:46.525
 Insufficient insulin production is not compatible with life. 

00:03:46.525 --> 00:03:49.181
 And insulin resistance, as the name suggests, 

00:03:49.181 --> 00:03:51.861
 occurs when cells become more and more resistant 

00:03:51.861 --> 00:03:55.374
 from the effects of insulin trying to do its job. 

00:03:55.374 --> 00:03:57.550
 When you become insulin resistant, 

00:03:57.550 --> 00:03:58.925
 you become diabetic, 

00:03:58.925 --> 00:04:00.989
 what happens when the pancreas 

00:04:00.989 --> 00:04:04.312
 cannot withstand resistance and produce enough insulin. 

00:04:04.312 --> 00:04:06.940
 The increase in the amount of sugar in the blood begins, 

00:04:06.940 --> 00:04:09.572
 and a waterfall of pathological problems 

00:04:09.572 --> 00:04:13.273
 get out of control, which can lead to heart problems, 

00:04:13.273 --> 00:04:16.882
 cancer, or even Alzheimer's, 

00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:21.764
 and amputation, just like that woman a few years ago. 

00:04:21.764 --> 00:04:24.725
 With this problem, I started to drastically change my diet, 

00:04:24.725 --> 00:04:26.902
 removing and adding things you would find 

00:04:26.902 --> 00:04:29.982
 obviously shocking. 

00:04:29.982 --> 00:04:33.861
 I did so and lost 20 kg, although I did less exercise. 

00:04:33.861 --> 00:04:36.902
 As you can see, I'm not overweight. 

00:04:36.902 --> 00:04:39.069
 What is more important is that I no longer have insulin resistance. 

00:04:39.069 --> 00:04:41.113
 But even more important are these three questions 

00:04:41.113 --> 00:04:44.962
 which I have left and which do not want to be taken away from me: 

00:04:44.962 --> 00:04:47.411
 How did this happen to me when I was thinking 

00:04:47.411 --> 00:04:50.108
 that I was doing everything right? 

00:04:50.108 --> 00:04:53.143
 If the science of healthy eating has been false, 

00:04:53.143 --> 00:04:56.930
 was that the case for others? 

00:04:56.930 --> 00:04:58.830
 And in analyzing these questions 

00:04:58.830 --> 00:05:02.076
 it became almost fixed 

00:05:02.076 --> 00:05:04.803
 in trying to understand the real connection 

00:05:04.803 --> 00:05:08.433
 between obesity and insulin resistance. 

00:05:08.433 --> 00:05:11.249
 Now, many researchers believe that obesity 

00:05:11.249 --> 00:05:14.641
 is due to insulin resistance. 

00:05:14.641 --> 00:05:16.756
 Logically, when treating insulin resistance, 

00:05:16.756 --> 00:05:18.648
 it forces people to lose weight, doesn't it? 

00:05:18.648 --> 00:05:21.412
 Treats obesity. 

00:05:21.412 --> 00:05:24.118
 What if it's the exact opposite? 

00:05:24.118 --> 00:05:27.489
 What if obesity is not the cause of insulin resistance? 

00:05:27.489 --> 00:05:31.409
 In fact, if it were a synthesis of a much bigger problem, 

00:05:31.409 --> 00:05:34.231
 the tip of an iceberg? 

00:05:34.231 --> 00:05:36.874
 I know it sounds a little weird, because we're in the middle 

00:05:36.874 --> 00:05:40.093
 of an obesity epidemic, but listen to me a little. 

00:05:40.093 --> 00:05:43.307
 What if obesity is a camouflage 

00:05:43.307 --> 00:05:46.909
 of a much more serious problem that 

00:05:46.909 --> 00:05:48.391
 does it have roots in the cell? 

00:05:48.391 --> 00:05:50.757
 I am not suggesting here that obesity is benign, 

00:05:50.757 --> 00:05:53.060
 but what I am suggesting is that it may be the least evil 

00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:55.771
 of the two evils of metabolism. 

00:05:55.771 --> 00:05:58.790
 You can think of insulin resistance as a limited ability 

00:05:58.790 --> 00:06:00.777
 of itself to distribute fuel, 

00:06:00.777 --> 00:06:03.068
 as I referred to a minute ago, 

00:06:03.068 --> 00:06:04.990
 to get the calories we provide with food 

00:06:04.990 --> 00:06:08.429
 and proportionally burn one part and store the other. 

00:06:08.429 --> 00:06:10.071
 When we become insulin resistant, 

00:06:10.071 --> 00:06:13.438
 homeostasis in this type of balancing is disrupted. 

00:06:13.438 --> 00:06:15.566
 So now, when insulin tells the cell, 

00:06:15.566 --> 00:06:17.611
 I want to burn more energy 

00:06:17.611 --> 00:06:20.046
 how safe the cell considers it, in fact it responds, 

00:06:20.046 --> 00:06:24.478
 "No thanks, I'll save that energy." 

00:06:24.478 --> 00:06:26.380
 And since it is not found in fat cells 

00:06:26.380 --> 00:06:29.182
 those complex cellular machines found in other cells, 

00:06:29.182 --> 00:06:31.953
 is the best place to store them. 

00:06:31.953 --> 00:06:36.922
 Many of us, about 75 million Americans, 

00:06:36.922 --> 00:06:40.537
