00:06:40.537 --> 00:06:45.466
 it may be to preserve it in the form of fat and not the other way around, 

00:06:45.466 --> 00:06:50.810
 to have insulin resistance in response to fat. 

00:06:50.810 --> 00:06:52.985
 This is actually a small change, 

00:06:52.985 --> 00:06:56.352
 but with serious consequences. 

00:06:56.352 --> 00:06:58.850
 Consider the following analogy: 

00:06:58.850 --> 00:07:01.819
 Think about the wrinkles you experience on the skin 

00:07:01.819 --> 00:07:05.411
 when you accidentally hit your knee on the coffee table. 

00:07:05.411 --> 00:07:08.298
 Obviously the wound hurts a lot and 

00:07:08.298 --> 00:07:11.279
 you don't like the fact that it's blackened, but we all know it 

00:07:11.279 --> 00:07:14.732
 that the wound itself is not the problem. 

00:07:14.732 --> 00:07:18.474
 In fact, it's the opposite, it's a healthy response to a trauma, 

00:07:18.474 --> 00:07:21.235
 it is the immune cells that run where the damage occurred 

00:07:21.235 --> 00:07:24.219
 to help the cells there and stop 

00:07:24.219 --> 00:07:26.917
 the spread of infection to other parts of the body. 

00:07:26.917 --> 00:07:30.639
 Now, imagine if we thought the wound was actually the problem, 

00:07:30.639 --> 00:07:33.507
 and conduct any research 

00:07:33.507 --> 00:07:36.647
 and medical culture about wound healing: 

00:07:36.647 --> 00:07:39.930
 camouflage cream, painkillers, and many more, 

00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.156
 completely ignoring the fact that people 

00:07:42.156 --> 00:07:45.776
 are still crashing into the coffee tables. 

00:07:45.776 --> 00:07:48.979
 How much better would it be if we treated the causes-- 

00:07:48.979 --> 00:07:50.544
 telling people to be more careful 

00:07:50.544 --> 00:07:52.147
 as they walk through the living room-- 

00:07:52.147 --> 00:07:55.420
 instead of the effect that is created? 

00:07:55.420 --> 00:07:57.297
 Understand the cause and effect, 

00:07:57.297 --> 00:07:59.776
 makes all possible difference. 

